<p><b>MythTV</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Free_software" title="Free software">free</a> <a href="/wiki/Linux" title="Linux">Linux</a> <sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> application which turns a computer with the necessary hardware into a <a href="/wiki/Computer_network" title="Computer network">network</a> <a href="/wiki/Streaming_media" title="Streaming media">streaming</a><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="/wiki/Digital_video_recorder" title="Digital video recorder">digital video recorder</a>, a <a href="/wiki/Digital" title="Digital">digital</a> <a href="/wiki/Multimedia" title="Multimedia">multimedia</a> <a href="/wiki/Home_entertainment_system" title="Home entertainment system" class="mw-redirect">home entertainment system</a>, or <a href="/wiki/HTPC" title="HTPC" class="mw-redirect">Home Theater Personal Computer</a>. It can be considered as a free and open source alternative to <a href="/wiki/Tivo" title="Tivo" class="mw-redirect">Tivo</a><sup id="cite_ref-post_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-post-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> or <a href="/wiki/Windows_Media_Center" title="Windows Media Center">Windows Media Center</a>.</p>
